<h2>My Travel Dreams</h2>
<p><img src="images/italy_2.webp" class="img-fluid" alt="Italy"></p>
<p>Sicily is the largest island in the Mediterranean and it is full of history, culture and incredible food. The ancient Greek temples at Agrigento are some of the best preserved in the world, even better than many in Greece itself. Sicily feels like a world within a world.</p>
<p>Venice is unlike any other city on the planet. Instead of roads there are canals, and instead of cars there are gondolas. Walking across the Rialto Bridge or sitting in St. Mark's Square with a coffee feels like stepping into another century entirely.</p>
<p>The Italian countryside is something that deserves its own mention. Rolling hills covered in vineyards and olive trees, small hilltop villages that have barely changed in hundreds of years — Tuscany in particular looks like a painting come to life. I would love to spend a week just driving through small towns with no particular plan.</p>
<p>Italian culture is also deeply rooted in family, food and celebration. Meals in Italy are not just about eating — they are long, social events where people gather for hours. The idea of sitting at a long table outside on a warm evening with fresh food and good company sounds like the perfect way to spend an evening.</p>
<p>One day I will make it to Italy. Whether it is for a week or a month, I know it is the kind of place that changes you. There is a reason millions of people visit every year and fall completely in love with it — it truly is one of the most beautiful countries in the world</p>





